ased on the number of people I expect to attend and the wide range of levels, I think the number of matches will be reasonable. If we get too many in a certain level bracket, we will do some kind of random matching. Too few, and there may be multiple engagements. Whoever has the highest win/loss ratio will be deemed the winner. Each round will start with a 3 minute buffing period. <br><br>The referee will choose 2 additional judges, hopefully one from each class in combat, to help with monitoring the duels and to recognize superior tactics. Points may be awarded for exceptional performances. <br><br><br>Part II<br>From 2:30 pm on will be the team event. This will be a test of team building and strategy. 2 team leaders will be chosen at random from those that want to be considered. Team members will be chosen from those attending the event. The flow of events will be as outlined below.<br><br>1. Pick 2 team captains. Just for an example Kedawen (50) and Tenador (47).<br>2. These captains take turns picking group members, with the selection changing every time one team out-levels the other. For Example, Tenador starts (since he is lower) and picks Gordoo (56) His total team level is now 103. Kedawen than chooses players as long as the total levels don’t exceed 103. For example, Fyrviel (43) and Legeran (41), giving a total of 134. Choice then returns to Tenador. <br>3. The leader then has 5 minutes to instruct their team. The team is to follow the leader’s instructions to the best of their ability, and should not debate the leader’s strategy. Hopefully the leader has observed the individual duels and has a good idea of people’s capabilities. <br>4. Each team will have a 3 minute buffing period.<br>5. Fight commences One leader is allowed to use the AUC channel for instructions, the other the OOC channel. Both teams can have both channels open. (Like a general shouting orders over the battle). The referee will use the shout channel. Guild chat will be used as it normally is, since there may be guild members online that are not attending the event.<br>6. Count the number of the winning team still standing, that is their score. There is no particular advantage to killing the leader, only total surviving body count is considered. Ties will be decided by another match.<br><br>Additional rules for team play:<br><br>1. No rezzing people back into battle.<br>2. Once killed, players must remain on the sidelines and keep quiet, except the leader, who may still shout instructions from the sidelines if killed. <br>3. No component based spells used on team members. One pet spell may be cast per battle.<br>4. Arrows can only be used if they are summoned during the buffing period.<br><br>Please come at your convienance and party hardy. <p><IMG SRC = http://www.faydwer.com/everquest/images/signatures/Azzlano.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub34.ezboard.com/fnorrathianbrotherhoodfrm21.showMessage?topicID=117.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub34.ezboard.com/fnorrathianbrotherhoodfrm21.showMessage?topicID=113.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub34.ezboard.com/fnorrathianbrotherhoodfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub34.ezboard.com/fnorrathianbrotherhoodfrm21.emailToFriend?topicID=115.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub34.ezboard.com/fnorrathianbrotherhoodfrm21.threadControl?topicID=115.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br>